Preheat the broiler to high or the oven to 500 degrees. In a #small pot{}, bring @water{1%cup} and the @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1} to a boil. Zest and halve the @Lime{1}. Cut the @Chicken Thighs{12%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Once boiling, add the @Basmati Rice{½%cup} to the pot, cover, and simmer for ~{15%minutes} until tender.

== Yogurt Sauce ==

Make the yogurt sauce: in a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Yogurt{5.3%ounce}, lime zest, @Tandoori Spice{1%tablespoon}, and @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place 1/3 of the yogurt sauce in a separate #small bowl{}, stir in @water{2%tablespoons} to thin it out, then set it aside. Toss the chicken into the remaining 2/3 yogurt sauce and let it marinate.

== Julienned Apple Salad ==

Prep the remaining ingredients: halve and thinly slice the @Scallions{2} lengthwise into very thin matchsticks. Halve, seed, and thinly slice the @Roma Tomato{1} into strips. Roughly chop the @Cilantro{¼%ounce} leaves and stems, keeping both separate. Core the @Apple{1}, then slice into thin matchsticks.

Make the julienned apple salad: in a medium bowl, combine the scallions, tomatoes, apple, cilantro stems, @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}, and the juice of the lime. Season with salt and pepper.

== Cooking the Chicken ==

Place the chicken on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Place in the oven for ~{7-10%minutes}, rotating sheet halfway through cooking, until cooked through and slightly charred.

When the rice is tender, fluff with a #fork{} and mix in half of the chopped cilantro leaves.

Plate the rice and chicken alongside the julienned apple salad. Drizzle the plate with the remaining yogurt sauce and garnish with the remaining cilantro. Enjoy!